{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"},"metadata":{"externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus","roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"}],"title":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"ScanbotSDK"}]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"(SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optical character recognition (OCR) invariably introduces errors in the recognized text."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There are numerous ways to verify that what has been recognized is, in fact, what was"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"written in the document."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The best way to validate the value of a field is for it to have a known format or validation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"logic. For example, an IBAN number has a known format and two check digits that make it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"very unlikely that a value with OCR errors will pass validation. Fields with known"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"validation rules will have a validation status of either VALID or INVALID."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fields whose value can be inferred from other fields, or from domain knowledge (for example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the field may have the same value in every instance of this type of document), will have the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"status INFERRED. Inferring the value of a field is a strong validation method, provided that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"there are no unexpected changes to the document format."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fields that do not have validation rules and cannot be inferred can still be validated by checking whether the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value is recognized from multiple attempts, e.g. across multiple frames of a camera stream."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the same value is recognized in multiple frames, the value is considered CONFIRMED, otherwise"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it will have the status NONE. This is the least strict validation method, as it does not protect"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from systemic OCR errors, but in practice it still provides good results for most fields."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkgenericdocumentfieldvalidationstatus"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkgenericdocumentfieldvalidationstatus"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus\/ra